# Deployment Guide — {{ project_id }}

> Generated by Fine-Tuning OS. Adapt to your infrastructure before use.

---

## Prerequisites

| Requirement | Minimum | Recommended |
|-------------|---------|-------------|
| GPU VRAM | 16 GB | 24–80 GB |
| RAM | 32 GB | 64 GB |
| Storage | 100 GB | 500 GB SSD |
| CUDA | 12.1+ | 12.3+ |
| Docker | 24.0+ | latest |
| OS | Ubuntu 22.04 | Ubuntu 24.04 |

---

## Step 1 — Pull or Build the Inference Image

```bash
# Option A: build locally
docker build -t ftos-{{ project_id }}-infer:latest \
  -f docker/Dockerfile.infer .

# Option B: pull from registry (if pre-built)
docker pull $FTOS_REGISTRY/ftos-{{ project_id }}-infer:latest
```

---

## Step 2 — Prepare the Model

```bash
# Mount the merged/quantized model at /models
export MODEL_DIR=/path/to/merged-model
```

---

## Step 3 — Configure Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file (never commit to git):

```
API_KEY=<your-api-key>
MODEL_PATH=/models/{{ project_id }}-merged
PORT={{ port | default(8000) }}
```

---

## Step 4 — Run the Container

```bash
docker run -d \
  --name ftos-infer-{{ project_id }} \
  --gpus '"device={{ gpu_device | default("all") }}"' \
  -p {{ port | default(8000) }}:{{ port | default(8000) }} \
  -v "$MODEL_DIR":/home/inferuser/models:ro \
  --env-file .env \
  --restart unless-stopped \
  ftos-{{ project_id }}-infer:latest
```

> **Security**: `--restart unless-stopped` ensures availability; use
> `--read-only` + tmpfs for the model volume if stricter isolation is needed.

---

## Step 5 — Health Check

```bash
curl http://localhost:{{ port | default(8000) }}/health
# Expected: {"status": "ok"}
```

---

## Step 6 — TLS / Reverse Proxy (Production)

For production, front the container with nginx or Caddy for TLS termination:

```nginx
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    server_name {{ api_hostname | default("api.example.com") }};

    ssl_certificate     /etc/ssl/certs/api.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/ssl/private/api.key;

    location /v1/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:{{ port | default(8000) }}/v1/;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }
}
```

---

## Step 7 — Monitoring

```bash
# Container logs
docker logs -f ftos-infer-{{ project_id }}

# GPU utilisation
nvidia-smi dmon -s u -d 5
```

---

## Rollback Procedure

```bash
docker stop ftos-infer-{{ project_id }}
docker rm   ftos-infer-{{ project_id }}
# Run Step 4 with the previous image tag
```

---

## Security Notes

- API keys are injected at runtime via environment variables — never baked into the image.
- Model weights are mounted read-only (`ro`) to prevent container modification.
- Run as non-root user `inferuser` (UID auto-assigned by image).
- Network access: only expose port {{ port | default(8000) }} on the host interface.
